My pages on Arabic may now be out of date (like most of my tutorial 
pages).  I am in the middle of setting up an Arabic experiment with Sami 
Boudelaa on a new laptop with Win2000 and some things now appear to work 
different.  Once we have things sorted out I will create a new page for 
Arabic and Win2000.  For a start, WordPad seems to behave a bit different 
with Arabic in Arabic Enable Windows 2000.  The "ignore unknown RTF" 
utility also changes things (makes them easier).

Not tried XP, but maybe the solutions we find for Win2000 will help with XP.

In a month or so's time I will hopefully have time to redo my tutorial 
pages.

- Mike

